[SN]TITLE[SN]
Coma judo star Stephanie Inglis has surgery in Bangkok

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Commonwealth Games silver medallist Stephanie Inglis' "brain is healing" following an operation in a hospital in Thailand, her family has said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The judo athlete suffered head injuries in a motorbike taxi accident in Vietnam on 10 May.
The 27-year-old has been in a coma since and also developed pneumonia.
She was flown to Bangkok last week and taken to a hospital equipped to treat her. Her family said the surgery went well and the pneumonia was improving.
Ms Inglis, from Inverness, won her silver medal at Glasgow 2014.
